    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="284"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Walter S. Robertson</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="63" xml:id="d284fn63">American Commissioner at Executive Headquarters,
                        Peiping.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-11">11 March
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>810. Subject is the Canton situation. Conditions as reported in our 328, 357 and
                    495 remain unchanged.<note n="64" xml:id="d284fn64">February 11, 13, and 24,
                            <ref target="#pg_430">pp. 430</ref>, <ref target="#pg_433">433</ref>,
                        and <ref target="#pg_441">441</ref>, respectively.</note> We still have no
                    indication that General Chang Fa Kwei recognizes either the authority of the
                    Executive Headquarters or the presence of Communist troops in his area. The
                    position of our team there is untenable as they have been able to accomplish
                    nothing during their stay of approximately 6 weeks. Believe you have all
                    background information concerning situation. Request action by the Committee of
                    Three to break stalemate before your departure for United States.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
